  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Human Rights Defenders - Defending Lives and Guaranteeing rights denied</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aim is to implement actions to protect the lives of human rights defenders (HRD) through the creation of protection network at local, state and at regional levels, strengthening security procedures in local grassroots organizations and social movements, raising awareness in target communities to protect HRDs and assisting with legal support for HRDs under threats. Beneficiaries are: small farmers, landless and indigenous people, fisherman/women, quilombolas, people living and working on the streets (catadores, ambulantes, sex workers and  homeless). Through activities of self protection and secure communication workshops, legal and emergency support for HRDs at high risk this proposal seeks to reduce the number of killing of HRDs.
CAFOD is contributing 10K to this proposal. Manos Unidas, DKA and Fastenopfer are also funding this proposal and Misereor has a larger project with SMDDH on HRD. This joint initiate was agree in the last meeting of the Brazil/CIDSE Working Group in Brasilia 2017.</narrative>
  </description>
